## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="aa6b2-1176">当<xref:System.Diagnostics.Process>将文本写入其标准的流，通常在控制台上显示文本。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="aa6b2-1176">When a <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process> writes text to its standard stream, that text is normally displayed on the console.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="aa6b2-1177">通过将重定向<xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A>流，你可以操作或取消进程的输出。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="aa6b2-1177">By redirecting the <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A> stream, you can manipulate or suppress the output of a process.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="aa6b2-1178">例如，你可以筛选文本、 格式设置不同，或将输出写入控制台和一个指定的日志文件。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="aa6b2-1178">For example, you can filter the text, format it differently, or write the output to both the console and a designated log file.</span></span>  
  
> [!NOTE]
>  <span data-ttu-id="aa6b2-1179">若要使用<xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A>，必须设置<xref:System.Diagnostics.ProcessStartInfo.UseShellExecute%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType>到`false`，并且必须设置<xref:System.Diagnostics.ProcessStartInfo.RedirectStandardOutput%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType>到`true`。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="aa6b2-1179">To use <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A>, you must set <xref:System.Diagnostics.ProcessStartInfo.UseShellExecute%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> to `false`, and you must set <xref:System.Diagnostics.ProcessStartInfo.RedirectStandardOutput%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> to `true`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="aa6b2-1180">否则，读取从<xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A>流时将引发异常。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="aa6b2-1180">Otherwise, reading from the <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A> stream throws an exception.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="aa6b2-1181">重定向<xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A>可以读取流，同步或异步。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="aa6b2-1181">The redirected <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A> stream can be read synchronously or asynchronously.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="aa6b2-1182">等方法<xref:System.IO.StreamReader.Read%2A>， <xref:System.IO.StreamReader.ReadLine%2A>，和<xref:System.IO.StreamReader.ReadToEnd%2A>同步对执行读取的操作过程的输出流。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="aa6b2-1182">Methods such as <xref:System.IO.StreamReader.Read%2A>, <xref:System.IO.StreamReader.ReadLine%2A>, and <xref:System.IO.StreamReader.ReadToEnd%2A> perform synchronous read operations on the output stream of the process.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="aa6b2-1183">这些同步读取操作不会完成之前关联<xref:System.Diagnostics.Process>写入其<xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A>流处理时，或关闭流。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="aa6b2-1183">These synchronous read operations do not complete until the associated <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process> writes to its <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A> stream, or closes the stream.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="aa6b2-1184">与此相反，<xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.BeginOutputReadLine%2A>开始异步读取操作上<xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A>流。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="aa6b2-1184">In contrast, <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.BeginOutputReadLine%2A> starts asynchronous read operations on the <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A> stream.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="aa6b2-1185">此方法将启用流输出指定的事件处理程序并立即返回到调用方，流输出定向到事件处理程序时可以执行其他工作。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="aa6b2-1185">This method enables a designated event handler for the stream output and immediately returns to the caller, which can perform other work while the stream output is directed to the event handler.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="aa6b2-1186">同步读取操作引入读取从调用方之间的依赖项<xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A>流和子进程的写入该流。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="aa6b2-1186">Synchronous read operations introduce a dependency between the caller reading from the <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A> stream and the child process writing to that stream.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="aa6b2-1187">这些依赖关系可能会导致死锁条件。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="aa6b2-1187">These dependencies can result in deadlock conditions.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="aa6b2-1188">当调用方读取子进程的重定向流时，它是依赖于子。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="aa6b2-1188">When the caller reads from the redirected stream of a child process, it is dependent on the child.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="aa6b2-1189">调用方上读取操作会一直等到子写入流或关闭流。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="aa6b2-1189">The caller waits on the read operation until the child writes to the stream or closes the stream.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="aa6b2-1190">子进程在编写时数据不足，无法填充其重定向的流，它是依赖于父。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="aa6b2-1190">When the child process writes enough data to fill its redirected stream, it is dependent on the parent.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="aa6b2-1191">子进程一直等到下一步的写入操作上的父项从完整的流中读取或关闭流。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="aa6b2-1191">The child process waits on the next write operation until the parent reads from the full stream or closes the stream.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="aa6b2-1192">当调用方和子进程互相等待来完成操作，并且都可以继续执行，死锁条件的结果。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="aa6b2-1192">The deadlock condition results when the caller and child process wait on each other to complete an operation, and neither can proceed.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="aa6b2-1193">可以通过评估的调用方和子进程之间的依赖关系来避免死锁。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="aa6b2-1193">You can avoid deadlocks by evaluating dependencies between the caller and child process.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="aa6b2-1194">下面的 C# 代码，例如，演示如何从重定向流中读取并等待子进程退出。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="aa6b2-1194">The following C# code, for example, shows how to read from a redirected stream and wait for the child process to exit.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
Process p = new Process();  
p.StartInfo.UseShellExecute = false;  
p.StartInfo.RedirectStandardOutput = true;  
p.StartInfo.FileName = "Write500Lines.exe";  
p.Start();  
  
// To avoid deadlocks, always read the output stream first and then wait.  
string output = p.StandardOutput.ReadToEnd();  
p.WaitForExit();  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="aa6b2-1195">下面的代码示例通过调用来避免死锁条件`p.StandardOutput.ReadToEnd`之前`p.WaitForExit`。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="aa6b2-1195">The code example avoids a deadlock condition by calling `p.StandardOutput.ReadToEnd` before `p.WaitForExit`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="aa6b2-1196">如果父进程调用会导致死锁条件`p.WaitForExit`之前`p.StandardOutput.ReadToEnd`和子进程将足够多的文本以填充重定向的流。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="aa6b2-1196">A deadlock condition can result if the parent process calls `p.WaitForExit` before `p.StandardOutput.ReadToEnd` and the child process writes enough text to fill the redirected stream.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="aa6b2-1197">父进程将无限期地等待子进程退出。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="aa6b2-1197">The parent process would wait indefinitely for the child process to exit.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="aa6b2-1198">子进程将无限期地等待父从完整读取<xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A>流。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="aa6b2-1198">The child process would wait indefinitely for the parent to read from the full <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A> stream.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="aa6b2-1199">从标准输出和标准错误流读取所有文本时类似问题。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="aa6b2-1199">There is a similar issue when you read all text from both the standard output and standard error streams.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="aa6b2-1200">下面的 C# 代码，例如，执行对这两种流的读取的操作。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="aa6b2-1200">The following C# code, for example, performs a read operation on both streams.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
// To avoid deadlocks, use asynchronous read operations on at least one of the streams.  
// Do not perform a synchronous read to the end of both redirected streams.  
p.BeginOutputReadLine();  
string error = p.StandardError.ReadToEnd();  
p.WaitForExit();  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="aa6b2-1201">下面的代码示例通过执行异步上读取操作来避免死锁条件<xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A>流。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="aa6b2-1201">The code example avoids the deadlock condition by performing asynchronous read operations on the <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A> stream.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="aa6b2-1202">死锁条件结果如果父进程调用`p.StandardOutput.ReadToEnd`跟`p.StandardError.ReadToEnd`和子进程将足够多的文本以填充其错误流。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="aa6b2-1202">A deadlock condition results if the parent process calls `p.StandardOutput.ReadToEnd` followed by `p.StandardError.ReadToEnd` and the child process writes enough text to fill its error stream.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="aa6b2-1203">父进程将无限期地等待子进程以关闭其<xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A>流。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="aa6b2-1203">The parent process would wait indefinitely for the child process to close its <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A> stream.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="aa6b2-1204">子进程将无限期地等待父从完整读取<xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardError%2A>流。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="aa6b2-1204">The child process would wait indefinitely for the parent to read from the full <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardError%2A> stream.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="aa6b2-1205">异步读取的操作可用于避免这些依赖关系和其潜在的死锁。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="aa6b2-1205">You can use asynchronous read operations to avoid these dependencies and their deadlock potential.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="aa6b2-1206">或者，可以通过创建两个线程并读取在单独线程上的每个流的输出来避免出现死锁条件。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="aa6b2-1206">Alternately, you can avoid the deadlock condition by creating two threads and reading the output of each stream on a separate thread.</span></span>  
  
> [!NOTE]
>  <span data-ttu-id="aa6b2-1207">不能混合在重定向流上的异步和同步读取的操作。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="aa6b2-1207">You cannot mix asynchronous and synchronous read operations on a redirected stream.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="aa6b2-1208">一次的重定向的流<xref:System.Diagnostics.Process>打开在异步或同步模式下，所有进一步读取该流上的操作必须处于相同的模式。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="aa6b2-1208">Once the redirected stream of a <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process> is opened in either asynchronous or synchronous mode, all further read operations on that stream must be in the same mode.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="aa6b2-1209">例如，不遵循<xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.BeginOutputReadLine%2A>通过调用<xref:System.IO.StreamReader.ReadLine%2A>上<xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A>流，反之亦然。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="aa6b2-1209">For example, do not follow <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.BeginOutputReadLine%2A> with a call to <xref:System.IO.StreamReader.ReadLine%2A> on the <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardOutput%2A> stream, or vice versa.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="aa6b2-1210">但是，你可以读取在不同模式下的两个不同的流。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="aa6b2-1210">However, you can read two different streams in different modes.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="aa6b2-1211">例如，你可以调用<xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.BeginOutputReadLine%2A>，然后调用<xref:System.IO.StreamReader.ReadLine%2A>为<xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardError%2A>流。</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="aa6b2-1211">For example, you can call <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.BeginOutputReadLine%2A> and then call <xref:System.IO.StreamReader.ReadLine%2A> for the <xref:System.Diagnostics.Process.StandardError%2A> stream.</span></span>  
  
   
  
